{
  "text": "Blood pressure (BP) was measured with an oscillometric monitor as described [CITATION_1] . Hypertension was defined as BP !130/85 mmHg [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] or use of antihypertensive drugs. Glycated haemoglobin (HbA 1c ) was measured by HPLC, serum and urinary creatinine by the Jaffe's reaction and albumin excretion rate (AER) by a fluorimetric assay [CITATION_4] in three 24-h urine collections. Patients were classified as normoalbuminuric (AER <20 mg/min), microalbuminuric (AER 20-200 mg/min) or proteinuric (AER >200 mg/min) [CITATION_5] . Patients who were microalbuminuric or proteinuric before antihypertensive treatment were classified according to their pre-treatment AER values. GFR was estimated by the mean of three 24-h creatinine clearances which are highly correlated (R \u00bc 0.92; P < 0.001) with inulin clearances performed during the same GCRC admission [CITATION_6] . Retinopathy was assessed by fundoscopy [CITATION_7] . RNA isolation. The modified single-step isolation method [CITATION_8] was used to extract SF total RNA and the quantity and quality determined as described [11] . No samples required exclusion for RNA degradation. Total RNA was adjusted to 0.05 g/L and aliquots frozen at \u00c0708C in RNA Storage Solution (Ambion Inc, Austin, Texas) containing 20 U/ml of SUPERase In \u00d5 (Ambion Inc, Austin, Texas) until assayed. Pooled total RNA from SF of six normal subjects was the 'reference' standard. A set of eight 2-fold serial dilutions of the 0.4 ng/ml RNA standard was prepared and stored in aliquots at \u00c0708C until used.",
  "correct_citation": {
